The paper discusses improvements to the Differentiable Neural Computer (DNC), which is a type of neural network used for algorithmic and question answering tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses improvements to memory allocation and addressing, which are common topics in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the bAbI question answering dataset, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses improvements to arithmetic tasks, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the tasks involve image processing.
